["Grande Rio Br\u00e9scia Clube, commonly known as Br\u00e9scia, is a Brazilian football club based in Mag\u00e9, Rio de Janeiro state. The club was formerly known as Associa\u00e7\u00e3o Desportiva Grande Rio.","The club was founded on May 1, 1982,[1] as Associa\u00e7\u00e3o Desportiva Grande Rio.[2] After starting a partnership with Italian club Brescia Calcio in 1999, the club was renamed to Grande Rio Br\u00e9scia Clube and adopted similar logo, kits and colors.[2] The partnership ended in 2006, after one of its supporters died, but the club kept the similar logo, kits and colors.[2]","Grande Rio Br\u00e9scia Clube play their home games at Est\u00e1dio Manoel dos Reis.[1] The stadium has a maximum capacity of 5,000 people.[1]"]